#: ../../../release_details/9.4/python-numpy-integration.md:1
msgid "Numpy integration improvements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/python-numpy-integration.md:3
msgid "Add Python logic to enable module import at vtk module load"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/python-numpy-integration.md:5
msgid ""
"This feature is mostly driven by the @override capability in Python to "
"automatically enhance native vtk class with some Python one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/python-numpy-integration.md:7
msgid "By default we have added those following dependencies:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/python-numpy-integration.md:8
msgid "vtkCommonDataModel: vtkmodules.util.data_model"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/python-numpy-integration.md:9
msgid "vtkCommonExecutionModel: vtkmodules.util.execution_model"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/python-numpy-integration.md:11
msgid ""
"But now a user is able to add to it by calling `vtkmodules."
"register_vtk_module_dependencies(vtk_module_name, *import_strings)` to "
"automate imports at vtk module loading."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/python-numpy-integration.md:13
msgid "Make numpy optional for vtkmodules.util.data_model"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/python-numpy-integration.md:15
msgid ""
"`vtkmodules.util.data_model` has been added to enhance vtkDataModel API for "
"Python using the @override infrastructure to mainly handle numpy in/out "
"manipulation. But since numpy is an optional dependency for VTK, we are "
"providing a downgraded version when numpy is not available so we can keep "
"automatically load it at module startup regardless of numpy presence."
msgstr ""
